As of today, it has not been definitively proven that any drug is suitable for treating the existing infection caused by Ebola, even though there is an experimental vaccine that appears to be capable of reducing the mortality caused by this disease.
Zmapp, a combination of antibodies, had a promising field result at first, but formal studies showed that it was less beneficial than expected in preventing death.
In the PALM trial, the function of Zmapp was as a control, meaning that the scientists used it as a basis and compared it with the other three treatments.
USA Gymnastics supports the statement from the United States Olympic Committee and recognizes that it is imperative that the Olympic family fosters a safe environment for all our athletes.
We agree with the USOC's statement that the interests of the athletes, the clubs, and their sports, can be better served if we proceed with significant changes within our organization, rather than the withdrawal of certifications.
USA Gymnastics supports an independent investigation that can clarify how the abuse of the scale that Larry Nassar's survivors bravely described could have gone unnoticed for so long, and accepts any necessary and appropriate changes.
The goal of USA Gymnastics and USOC is the same: to make gymnastics and other sports as safe as possible so that athletes can pursue their dreams in a protected, positive, and empowered environment.
During the 60s, Brzezinski worked for John F. Kennedy as an advisor and, subsequently, for the government of Lyndon B. Johnson.
