It was discovered that the sun was governed by the same basic principles as other stars: the only factors driving its activity within the system were its luminosity and its rotation.
The intensity of light and rotation combine to calculate a star's Rossby number, linked to the flow of plasma.
The lower the Rossby number, the lower the star's activity in relation to its magnetic inversions.
